reviewText: I tried to watch this show when it was on TV and we had satellite couldn't get past a few episodes; thought I'd try it again with internet TV since my choices are a little more limited --- I watched all of season 1 then the first couple of season 2 --- I just don't like the show, the part that Smith plays is too all over the room, as a nurse I should see her doing more nurse stuff --- I don't care if she is a director of nursing. I was a director of a division and I actually did the work too of my employees, how many times I filled in :) --- I am sorry to say that I don't think Smith's heart was in this either or maybe she is just that bad of an actress because I just couldn't connect to her or her character.
summary: I just don't care for this show

reviewText: I love this show, because in the world we live in people just don't do all they can for you; but Jada you did it, you would always go out of your way to help people, and followed through until the end.  That is the way the world should be, not just people you know but people in general.  I love watching Hawthorne and I wish it would stay on longer.  I will (God's will) watch it ALWAYS.  This show was the reason I got cable.  I did without cable for 2 years and I saw this advertisting and said ok, I am going to try it and I loved it.  Thanks TNT for giving me something to enjoy.

reviewText: A lot of action along with a lot of crises occur in this season two of Hawthorne.  The energy level is non stop for Christina (Jada Pinkett Smith) as she "runs" the hospital seemingly by herself with her very savy character as CNO.  A love triangle develops which threatens Christina's new marriage.  It ain't easy being a single Mom of a teenage daughter,  widowed,  and keeping all in order at the hospital.  Christina pulls it off and makes it look easy.  This is an adult medical series I think your going to enjoy.
summary: Hospital and actors are in a crisis phase

reviewText: I tried to keep up with this show, while it was on TNT, but the "powers that be" kept moving the show to different days and hours, and I couldn't keep up. Then the show was cancelled. So, I decided to purchase the series, and my husband and I were instantly hooked. We watched the first season and the second season all in one evening. Jada and the supporting cast really delivers. This show should still be on the air for all to enjoy.
